<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Mariner Players Injured  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE (AP) -- The Mariners lost three starting position players
and starting pitcher Freddy Garcia in Friday night's game against
the Kansas City Royals.
</P>
<P>
   Center fielder Mike Cameron was knocked out with a bruised knee.
He was hit by a foul ball from Dan Wilson while standing in the
on-deck circle in the second inning.
</P>
<P>
   Mark McLemore was moved from left to center and Stan Javier was
inserted in left by Seattle manager Lou Piniella at the start of
the third.
</P>
<P>
   The right-handed Garcia left the game with a sore right knee in
the third. He was injured when he attempted to cover first on
Johnny Damon's ground ball to lead off the inning.
</P>
<P>
   The Mariners lost their third starter when John Mabry pulled his
right groin muscle while trying to field Jermaine Dye's hit in the
third. He came out in the top of the fourth.
</P>
<P>
   Designed hitter Edgar Martinez had to leave the game in the
fifth because of a sore left quadriceps muscle. He was hurt in the
third after he had an RBI groundout.
</P>
</TEXT>
