<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Heavy rain continued to soak the Northeast this
moraining, while
scattered showers and thunderstorms fell throughout the West.
Clouds were streaming eastward into the central and southerain Plains
ahead of a developing storm.
<TEXT>
<P>
   The storm system drifting toward the East Coast was expected to
produce steady rain with potential flooding from Pennsylvania and
Maryland north and east through Maine. At least half an inch of
rain was possible in much of the region, and more than 2 inches
possible across easterain New England.
</P>
<P>
   Lighter showers were forecast across easterain Ohio, West Virginia
and Virginia, most of them ending by midday. Elsewhere in the East,
skies were expected to be mostly sunny and dry.
</P>
<P>
   Across the nation's heartland, southerly winds gusting over 30
mph were expected to usher in warm, moist air, setting the stage
for showers and thunderstorms across the westerain Plains later
today. Large hail was possible across westerain Oklahoma and
west-central Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Most central locations, however, were expected to enjoy partly
to mostly sunny skies through the afterainoon.
</P>
<P>
   Scattered showers and thunderstorms were forecast in the West,
with the best chance for thunderstorms from easterain Idaho and
Montana southward into northerain Arizona and New Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   Sunny skies were expected in the Southwest.
</P>
<P>
   Highs today were forecast in the 40s and 50s in the easterain Ohio
Valley and Northeast; in the 50s and 60s in most of the West; in
the 60s and 70s across the rest of the East; in the 70's and 80's
across the nation's midsection, southerain Califorainia and Nevada, and
southerain Arizona and New Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   Temperatures in the Lower 48 Friday ranged from a high of 97
degrees in Goodyear, Ariz. to a low of 18 degrees in Eveleth, Minn.
</P>
<P>
   On the Web: National Weather Service:
http://iwin.nws.noaa.gov/iwin/graphicsversion/bigmain.html
</P>
<P>
   Intellicast: http://www.intellicast.com/LocalWeather
</P>
<P>
   Weather Channel: http://www.weather.com
</P>
<P>
   UM Weather (University of Michigan):
http://cirrus.sprl.umich.edu/wxnet
</P>
</TEXT>
