   The event was to raise money to fight the Eagle Mountain
Landfill, which -- if built -- would be one of the country's largest
garbage dumps. Environmental groups have sued to stop the project,
which would be surrounded on three sides by the park.
</P>
<P>
   Pollution ''is a worldwide mega-problem, and with such a problem
you can only begin in your own back yard,'' the 58-year-old Palm
Springs resident said. ''That's why I'm fighting this. This is my
own back yard.''
