<HEADLINE> Sunday TV Talks Shows at a Glance  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Lineup for the Sunday TV news shows:
</P>
<P>
   ABC's ''This Week'' -- Topics: Elian Gonzalez and Earth Day's
30th anniversary. Guests: Former Solicitor-General Walter Dellinger
and Sen. Arlen Specter, R-Pa., and Lazaro family attorney Roger
Bernstein; and Earth Day's 30th anniversary, with Robert F.
Kennedy, Jr., of Riverkeepers, and Virginia Gov. James Gilmore.
</P>
<P>
   CBS' ''Face the Nation'' -- Topics: Elian Gonzalez and campaign
2000. Guests: Jose Garcia Pedrosa, attorney for Miami relatives of
Elian Gonzalez; Rep. Charles Rangel, D-N.Y.; John Harwood of the
Wall Street Jorunal; and William Kristol of the Weekly Standard.
</P>
<P>
   NBC's ''Meet the Press'' -- Topic: Elian Gonzalez; Earth Day,
politics; basketball, kids and values. Guests: Spencer Eig, an
attorney for the Gonzalez relatives; and Dr. Irwin Redlener,
pediatrician and consulatnt for the INS; Green Party presidential
hopeful Ralph Nader. Michael Jordan, NBA's Washington Wizards.
