<HEADLINE> India Tea Estate Manager Kills 5  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GAUHATI, India (AP) -- A tea estate manager allegedly shot at
workers who mobbed him Saturday to demand better wages, killing
five people and seriously wounding 20 others.
</P>
<P>
   The company official in the thickly forested Assam state,
India's tea hub, was joined by his security guards as they opened
fire at nearly 200 slogan-shouting laborers inside the Borgora tea
estate in the northern Darrang area, a district official said on
customary condition of anonymity.
</P>
<P>
   The workers demanded their daily wages be raised to 90 cents
from the current 70 cents.
</P>
<P>
   The official said four workers died immediately and one more in
hospital. Police have arrested the garden manager and his security
guards.
</P>
<P>
   Borgora is among the three gardens in Assam which produce green
tea.
</P>
