<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seattle Puts Two More on DL  </HEADLINE>
By JIM COUR, AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE (AP) -- Already without No. 1 starter Jamie Moyer, the
Seattle Mariners placed No. 2 starter Freddy Garcia on the 15-day
disabled list on Saturday after a rash of injuries sidelined four
Mariners players the previous night.
</P>
<P>
   ''They were pretty rapid fire, weren't they?'' manager Lou
Piniella said the day after he lost Garcia, John Mabry, Edgar
Martinez and Mike Cameron in the first three innings of a 10-2
victory over Kansas City.
</P>
<P>
   Garcia, a 17-game winner who was runnerup in the AL Rookie of
the Year voting last season, probably has bursitis in his right
leg, a condition he might have aggravated Friday night when he
attempted to cover first in the third inning.
</P>
<P>
   Garcia was taken to a hospital on Saturday to have X-rays to
determine if he had a stress fracture in his right tibia, team
medical director Dr. Larry Pedegana said. If he has a stress
fracture, he will be sidelined 4-6 weeks, Pedegana said.
</P>
<P>
   ''On top of Moyer, you lose Garcia, the top two pitchers in your
rotation,'' Piniella said. ''We're fortunate we have some depth.''
</P>
<P>
   Also on Saturday, the Mariners placed Mabry, a valuable utility
player who is a left-handed hitter, on the 15-day DL because of a
severe groin pull in his right leg, sustained while attempting to
field a ball in the third.
</P>
<P>
   The Mariners recalled right-hander Kevin Hodges from Triple-A
Tacoma to take Garcia's place on the roster. After Seattle's 4-2
victory over Kansas City on Saturday, Piniella said Hodges would
start out in Seattle's bullpen.
</P>
<P>
   Although Piniella and pitching coach Bryan Price have not
decided who will start on Wednesday in Garcia's place, Piniella is
expected to bring right-hander Paul Abbott out of the bullpen to be
a starter.
</P>
<P>
   He said right-hander Frankie Rodriguez would remain in the
bullpen.
</P>
<P>
   After Friday night's game, the Mariners brought up utility
infielder Carlos Hernandez from Tacoma to take Mabry's place.
</P>
<P>
   When the Mariners put Moyer on the 15-day DL with a strained
muscle in the back of his left shoulder on Friday, they brought up
right-hander Brett Tomko from Tacoma to start Saturday's game
against the Royals.
</P>
<P>
   Piniella said Martinez (sore left quadriceps muscle) and Cameron
(bruised left knee) were expected to be able to play in Sunday's
game. Neither were available Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Carlos Guillen, who began the season as Seattle's starting third
baseman, was scheduled to begin a rehabilitation assignment in
Tacoma on Saturday night. Guillen was placed on the 15-day disabled
list on April 13 with a pulled left hamstring.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
