<HEADLINE> Cardinals Have 41 Home Runs in April  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. LOUIS (AP) -- An upper-deck shot by Mark McGwire in the first
inning Saturday night gave the St. Louis Cardinals 41 homers in
April, tying an NL record.
</P>
<P>
   McGwire hit his fourth home run, and first since April 10, off
Colorado's Masato Yoshii. The two-run drive landed just inside the
foul pole in left field and was estimated at 446 feet.
</P>
<P>
   The Cardinals tied the NL record set by the Atlanta Braves in
April 1998. The major league mark is 49 by Cleveland in 1997.
</P>
<P>
   The overall record for any month is 58 by Baltimore in May 1987.
</P>
