<HEADLINE> Cardinals Have 42 Home Runs in April  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Two-run shots by Mark McGwire in the first
inning and Fernando Tatis in the third gave the St. Louis Cardinals
an NL record 42 homers in April.
</P>
<P>
   McGwire hit his fourth home run, his first since April 10, off
Colorado's Masato Yoshii. The two-run drive landed just inside the
foul pole in left field and was estimated at 446 feet.
</P>
<P>
   Tatis hit his fifth of the season with two outs in the third,
also off Yoshii, although it took the umpires some time to award
it. Replays showed the ball cleared the left-field wall by several
feet before it bounced back on the field, but third-base umpire
Marty Foster signaled the ball was in play.
</P>
<P>
   Tatis was stopped at second base for several minutes before
Foster asked for help, Plate umpire Ron Kulpa over-ruled the call,
and Rockies manager Buddy Bell was ejected for arguing.
</P>
<P>
   The Atlanta Braves hit 41 home runs in April 1998. The major
league mark is 49 by Cleveland in 1997, and the overall record for
any month is 58 by Baltimore in May 1987.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
