<HEADLINE> Actor Brosnan's Son in Car Accident  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MALIBU, Calif. (AP) -- Actor Pierce Brosnan's 13-year-old son was
in a car that plunged 150-200 feet down a steep embankment early
Saturday, leaving him with multiple fractures and spinal injuries,
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Alcohol was a factor in the crash, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Sean Brosnan suffered multiple fractures and spinal injuries
when the vehicle went down a brush-covered embankment near Malibu,
the California Highway Patrol said.
</P>
<P>
   Brosnan was airlifted to UCLA Medical Center, where he underwent
surgery, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Pierce Brosnan, best known as the latest actor to play James
Bond, was contacted at his home in Malibu shortly after the
accident and accompanied his son in the helicopter, the CHP said.
</P>
<P>
   CHP Officer Karen Faciane said Brosnan was being treated for a
fractured pelvis, a possible fracture to a vertebra and a ruptured
bladder. She said he was recovering in the intensive care unit and
was in stable but serious condition.
</P>
<P>
   Hospital spokeswoman Roxanne Moster said the hospital did not
have any patient listed under Brosnan's name.
</P>
<P>
   The 1982 Chevrolet Blazer was carrying six people when it went
off Dume Mountain Way near Malibu at about 3:45 a.m., the CHP said.
</P>
<P>
   The driver, James Hall, 19, was arrested for investigation of
driving under the influence of alcohol and causing major injuries.
</P>
<P>
   Hall told authorities he swerved to avoid a large rock and went
off the road.
</P>
<P>
   ''The initial investigation indicates that in addition to the
driver, several of the passengers had been consuming alcoholic
beverages,'' the CHP said.
</P>
<P>
   The CHP said some passengers were not wearing seatbelts and were
thrown from the vehicle. Several passengers with minor injuries
hiked back up to the roadway and used a cellular telephone to call
for help.
</P>
</TEXT>
