<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Va. Plane Crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MOUNT JACKSON, Va. (AP) -- A couple flying from Michigan were
killed Saturday when their small airplane clipped power lines and
crashed in Shenandoah County, state police said.
</P>
<P>
   Gary and Marcia Wilson, of Millington, Mich., departed from
Caro, Mich., in the morning and were planning to refuel their
four-seat Beechcraft Bonanza in Charlottesville before continuing
on to Newport News in the southeastern portion of the state when
the plane crashed around 1 p.m., state police spokeswoman Lucy
Caldwell said.
</P>
<P>
   The plane came within 50 feet of striking a house. Wreckage and
debris from the plane, which Gary Wilson owned, was scattered for
about a mile, she said.
</P>
<P>
   The Wilsons apparently were headed to Newport News to visit
family over the Easter weekend.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators from the National Transportation Safety Board were
expected to arrive at the crash site by Sunday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
